headline: Walmart's 'advantage' that Target used to have: Q3 earnings preview
summary: Walmart (WMT) and Target (TGT) are among the retail giants set to report quarterly earnings results this week. The Consumer Collective Co-Founder and Managing Director Jessica Ramirez speaks with Julie Hyman about which of these two chain stores will come out stronger this past quarter, commenting on their consumer pricing strategies. Other chains releasing earnings results this week include Home Depot (HD), Lowe's (LOW), TJX Companies (TJX), and BJ's Wholesale Club (BJ).
